snippet: A series of explosions struck across Iraq amid worsening sectarian tensions before elections in April.
abstract: Several explosions across Iraq kill at least 26 people and wound 85 others, continuing spate of violence that has marked sectarian tensions and political turmoil.
lead_paragraph: A series of explosions struck across Iraq amid worsening sectarian tensions before elections in April.

headline.seo: Dozens Killed in Bombings Across Iraq
headline.main: At Least 26 Killed in Bombings Across Iraq
headline.print_headline: Iraq: Bombs Kill at Least 26 People
